<section id="mission">
  <div class="origin-wrap">
    <div><canvas id="origin-c" aria-hidden="true"></canvas></div>
    <div>
      <div class="s-eye">The origin</div>
      <h2 class="s-h">A daughter, her mom,<br />and <em>the waves</em></h2>
      <p class="s-p">
        Our founder took her mother — who is deafblind — to the beach. Her mother
        couldn't hear the waves. She couldn't see them. But she could
        <strong style="color:#fff;font-weight:500;">feel them.</strong>
      </p>
      <p class="s-p" style="margin-top:16px;">
        That moment became a company.
        <strong style="color:#fff;font-weight:500;">What if sound could be translated into touch?</strong>
        What if a deaf child could feel music? What if a deafblind person could feel
        when someone calls their name?
      </p>
      <p class="s-p" style="margin-top:16px;">
        Our founder is hard of hearing and visually impaired. She doesn't build for
        this community from the outside —
        <strong style="color:#fff;font-weight:500;">she understands it from within.</strong>
        That's not a talking point. That's our foundation.
      </p>
      <div class="quote-block" style="margin-top:32px;">
        <div class="q-text">
          "The most beautiful things in the world cannot be seen or heard — they must
          be felt with the heart."
        </div>
        <div class="q-attr">— Helen Keller &nbsp;·&nbsp; The inspiration behind AccessWave</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
